 and students of global development studies are well-aware that development is a difficult concept. This thought-provoking book offers them advice for the future of development studies and hope for the future of humankind.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEconomic development. 0aEconomic policy. 0aGlobal commons. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Developing & Emerging Countries.2bisacsh1 aBabcicky, Philipp, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBabones, Salvatore J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z9783111196213oZDB-23-BUPP0 cprintz978144730108040uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781447301103?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447301103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447301103/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-BUPPc1995d2013